%N A387262 a(n) is the denominator of the winning probability of the starting player to reach n points first in the game "Risk or Safety", assuming optimal play.
%C A387262 For more details see A387260 and A387261.
%e A387262 a(2) = 7: For n=2, the optimal strategy is never to stop, but always try to get two consecutive heads. The winning probability is 1/4*(1 + (3/4)^2 + (3/4)^4 + ...) = 4/7.
